  <div class="comment">
    <h3 class="title"><a href="/please-dont-videoblog-vlog#comment-4745" class="active">My inflated ego.</a></h3>    <div class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="http://www.youtube.com/saintskyler" rel="nofollow">Skyler Delamater</a> (not verified) on Fri, 2008-01-04 12:19.</div>
    <div class="content"><p>I don't care if you don't watch my vlog. I used to blog but i've become a vlogger instead because it brings me more personal satisfaction. Call it ego if you want but vanity can have a very intoxicating effect, and I love it!!! I'm new to the whole vlogging community, but what i've learned so far is that with the right material and the right drive and creativity, a person can get loads traffic. It's fun, plain and simple. I agree with Shivering Timbers. No harm, no foul. So if you're against the idea of vlogging, dont tune in. Vloggers set themselves up for more criticism because your more likely to look like an idiot on a vlog than on a blog. For that we should be applauded for bravery. I believe that Vlogging is the wave of the future with or without voice to text applications. This lot is just an example of resistance to progressive change.</p>
</div>
